  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6774.94 sitting below the GEX flip at 6787 in a PIN regime, dealers are currently net long gamma and will be buying this dip while providing stabilizing flow. The massive positive gamma wall at 6780 (+87.5B) creates a natural magnet effect just 5 handles above current levels, while the surge in GEX (40.5% in 5min) indicates rapidly increasing dealer stabilization pressure. Key levels to watch: 6765 downside support where dealers accelerate buying (-42B negative gamma), and the 6780-6800 zone where multiple large positive gamma walls (+87B, +71B) will cap upside momentum through dealer selling.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pulled back toward 6780 with limited downside below 6765.",
